  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink280-kilavi">puṇarntuṭaṉ pōkiya talaimakaṉ talaimakaḷaik karaṇavakaiyāṉ varaintāṉāka etirceṉṟa tōḻikku iṉi yāṉ ivaḷai varaintamai numarkkuṇartta vēṇṭum eṉṟāṉāka avaḷ colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> What [the confidante] said, when the hero, who had united and eloped [with the heroine], having formally married her according to proper procedure, said to the confidante who encountered him: “Now it is necessary to inform your people that I have married her.”
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink280">
<l>karuviraṉ mantik kallā vaṉpārp</l>
<l>piruveti rīrṅkaḻai yēṟic ciṟukōṉ</l>
<l>matipuṭaip patupōṟ ṟōṉṟu nāṭa</l>
<l>varaintaṉai nīyeṉak kēṭṭiyā</l>
<l>ṉuraittaṉe ṉalleṉō vaḵteṉ yāykkē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>O man from the land</l>
        <l>where the untaught, strong young</l>
        <l> of the black-fingered female monkey,</l>
        <l>having climbed the moist bamboo pole</l>
        <l>of the great bamboo,</l>
        <l>appeared to beat the moon—</l>
        <l>having heard that you have married her,</l>
        <l>would I not have told it to my mother?</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
